    def findFinalValue(self, nums: List[int], original: int) -> int:\n        nums_set = set(nums)  # Convert list to set for O(1) lookups\n        while original in nums_set:\n            original *= 2\n        return original\n```\n\nThis solution converts the list `nums` into a set `nums_set` to allow for O(1) average time complexity for lookups. The while loop continues to multiply `original` by 2 as long as `original` is found in `nums_set`. Once `original` is no longer found, the function returns the final value of `original`.", "estimated_date": 1643500800000}